Context:
This text provides information about an online information session for George Brown College's Business Administration – International Business Program (B131). The session aims to answer questions and give an overview of the program and future career options. Interested individuals are encouraged to sign up and learn more about the college's land acknowledgment, as well as stay updated on application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, and tours.

Contact information is available for those who may have additional questions: 416-415-2000 (main number), TTY: 1-877-515-5559 for the hearing impaired, or by email at ask.george@georgebrown.ca.

The text also includes a request to visit the college's social media hub and a disclaimer that the information contained in the website may be subject to change without notice. It is important to note that students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements themselves.
